org.epochx.stats
Class StatField

java.lang.Object
  org.epochx.stats.StatField
Direct Known Subclasses:
GEStatField, GPStatField, GRStatField
public class StatField
extends java.lang.Object

Provides constants to be used as keys to request statistics from the Stats.

RUN_NUMBER

public static final Stat RUN_NUMBER
Returns an Integer which is the sequential identifier of the last run in the series of runs. The first run will be run number 0.

RUN_TIME_H

Returns a Long which is the length of time in hours that the last run took to complete.

RUN_FITNESS_MIN

public static final Stat RUN_FITNESS_MIN
Returns a Double which is the lowest fitness score achieved by a CandidateProgram in the last run. Note that standardised fitness is used, so the best program has the minimum fitness.

RUN_FITTEST_PROGRAM

public static final Stat RUN_FITTEST_PROGRAM
Returns the CandidateProgram which obtained the fitness score in the RUN_FITNESS_MIN field.

INIT_REVERSIONS

public static final Stat INIT_REVERSIONS
Returns an Integer which is the number of times the last initialisation operation was reverted.

GEN_NUMBER

public static final Stat GEN_NUMBER
Returns an Integer which is the sequential identifier of the last generation where generation 0 is the initialisation phase.

GEN_FITNESSES

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESSES
Returns a double[] which contains the fitnesses of all the CandidatePrograms in the population at the end of the previous generation. The fitnesses are arranged in the same order as the List<CandidateProgram> returned for the GEN_POP field.

GEN_FITNESS_MIN

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESS_MIN
Returns a Double which is the lowest fitness score of a CandidateProgram in the last generation. Note that standardised fitness is used, so the best program has the minimum fitness.

GEN_FITNESS_MAX

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESS_MAX
Returns a Double which is the highest fitness score of a CandidateProgram in the last generation. Note that standardised fitness is used, so the best program has the minimum fitness.

GEN_FITNESS_AVE

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESS_AVE
Returns a Double which is the average fitness score of all the CandidatePrograms in the population at the end of the previous generation.

GEN_FITNESS_STDEV

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESS_STDEV
Returns a Double which is the standard deviation of the fitness scores of all the CandidatePrograms in the population at the end of the previous generation.

GEN_FITNESS_MEDIAN

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESS_MEDIAN
Returns a Double which is the median value of all the fitness scores from the population of CandidatePrograms at the end of the previous generation.

GEN_FITNESS_CI95

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESS_CI95
Returns a Double which is the 95% confidence interval either side of the fitness mean for the population of CandidatePrograms at the end of the previous generation.

GEN_FITTEST_PROGRAM

public static final Stat GEN_FITTEST_PROGRAM
Returns the CandidateProgram which obtained the fitness score in the GEN_FITNESS_MIN field. If more than one program obtained the same fitness then the one returned will be chosen arbitrarily. See the similarly named GEN_FITTEST_PROGRAMS field to obtain all the programs.

GEN_FITTEST_PROGRAMS

public static final Stat GEN_FITTEST_PROGRAMS
Returns a List<CandidateProgram> of all those programs which obtained the fitness score in the GEN_FITNESS_MIN field. See the similarly named GEN_FITTEST_PROGRAM field for returning just one CandidateProgram.

GEN_REVERSIONS

public static final Stat GEN_REVERSIONS
Returns an Integer which is the number of times the previous generation was reverted.

GEN_POP

public static final Stat GEN_POP
Returns a List<CandidateProgram> which is the population of CandidatePrograms at the end of the previous generation.

GEN_POP_SORTED

public static final Stat GEN_POP_SORTED
Returns a List<CandidateProgram> which is the population of CandidatePrograms at the end of the previous generation. The programs are sorted according to fitness ascending from lowest fitness score to highest.

GEN_POP_SORTED_DESC

public static final Stat GEN_POP_SORTED_DESC
Returns a List<CandidateProgram> which is the population of CandidatePrograms at the end of the previous generation. The programs are sorted according to fitness descending from highest fitness score to lowest.

GEN_FITNESSES_SORTED

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESSES_SORTED
Returns a double[] which contains the fitnesses of all the CandidatePrograms in the population at the end of the previous generation. The fitnesses are sorted in ascending order from lowest fitness score to highest. The order matches the the List<CandidateProgram> returned for the GEN_POP_SORTED field.

GEN_FITNESSES_SORTED_DESC

public static final Stat GEN_FITNESSES_SORTED_DESC
Returns a double[] which contains the fitnesses of all the CandidatePrograms in the population at the end of the previous generation. The fitnesses are sorted in descending order from highest fitness score to lowest. The order matches the List<CandidateProgram> returned for the GEN_POP_SORTED_DESC field.

GEN_TIME

public static final Stat GEN_TIME

MUT_PARENT_FITNESS

public static final Stat MUT_PARENT_FITNESS
Returns a Double which is the fitness score of the program selected for mutation prior to the mutation operation being performed.

MUT_CHILD_FITNESS

public static final Stat MUT_CHILD_FITNESS
Returns a Double which is the fitness score of the program selected for mutation after the mutation operation has been performed.

MUT_FITNESS_CHANGE

public static final Stat MUT_FITNESS_CHANGE
Returns a Double which is the amount by which the fitness of the mutated program has changed from before to after the operation. If the fitness has decreased then the returned value will be negative, if it has increased then it will be positive and it will be zero if the fitness is unchanged.

XO_PARENTS

public static final Stat XO_PARENTS
Returns a CandidateProgram[] which contains a copy of the programs which underwent crossover as they were before the crossover operation was applied.

XO_CHILDREN

public static final Stat XO_CHILDREN

public static final Stat XO_TIME
Returns a Long which is the length of time in nanoseconds that the last crossover operation took to complete.

XO_TIME_MS

public static final Stat XO_TIME_MS
Returns a Long which is the length of time in milliseconds that the last crossover operation took to complete.

XO_TIME_S

public static final Stat XO_TIME_S
Returns a Long which is the length of time in seconds that the last crossover operation took to complete.

XO_REVERSIONS

public static final Stat XO_REVERSIONS
Returns an Integer which is the number of times the last crossover operation was reverted.

XO_PARENT_FITNESSES

public static final Stat XO_PARENT_FITNESSES
Returns a double[] which is an array of the fitnesses of the programs selected for crossover prior to the crossover operation being performed. The order of the fitness scores is the same as for the CandidateProgram[] returned for the XO_PARENTS field.

XO_CHILD_FITNESSES

public static final Stat XO_CHILD_FITNESSES
Returns a double[] which is an array of the fitnes scores of the programs selected for crossover after the crossover operation has been performed. The order of the fitness scores is the same as for the CandidateProgram[] returned for the XO_CHILDREN field.

XO_PARENTS_FITNESS_AVE

public static final Stat XO_PARENTS_FITNESS_AVE
Returns a Double which is the average value of the fitnesses of the parents selected for crossover prior to the crossover operation being performed.

XO_CHILDREN_FITNESS_AVE

public static final Stat XO_CHILDREN_FITNESS_AVE
Returns a Double which is the average value of the fitnesses of the programs selected for crossover after the crossover operation has been performed.

XO_FITNESS_AVE_CHANGE

public static final Stat XO_FITNESS_AVE_CHANGE
Returns a Double which is the amount by which the average fitnesses of the crossed over programs has changed from before to after the operation. If the fitness has decreased then the returned value will be negative, if it has increased then it will be positive and it will be zero if the fitness is unchanged.

POOL_REVERSIONS

POOL_FITNESSES

public static final Stat POOL_FITNESSES
